  </header>
  
  <main class="homepage" id="home">
    <article class="hero-text-container">
      <h1 class="hero-secondary-header">Hello, My Name is</h1>
      <section class="name-container">
        <h1 class="hero-header secondary-color">Prabdeep</h1>
        <h1 class="hero-header ml-100" id="removeHeroHeaderMargin">Dhaliwal</h1>
      </section>
      <div>
        <h4 class="hero-secondary-header">&#8211; Full Stack Developer / Unity Game Developer</h4>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-20">
        <a href="#contact" class="anchor-btn">Contact Me</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <section class="vp-100 about" id="about">
    <img class="about-img" src="../imgs/Prab-Img.png" alt="Prabdeep Dhaliwal" height="350">
    <article class="about-section">
      <h3 class="secondary-header">Discover</h3>
      <h3 class="header">&#8211; About Me</h3>
      <p class="about-para">
        On September 2019, a couple months after graduating York University with a bachelors in Chemistry, 
        I had no idea that my life was about to change. I decided to open Unity for the first time, only 
        to find myself glued to the computer chair. I was spending as much time as I possibly could working 
        on an ambitious first project -- a large RPG game. After several months, I was very proud of my 
        progress, however, I realized that the project would take far too much time for a solo developer to 
        finish. So I quickly started a new project that I knew would be both challenging and one that I 
        could finish within a reasonable time frame. A couple months later, I was able to finish my first 
        project, a 3D tower defence game. With this new found passion and confidence, I was able to challenge 
        myself to learn HTML, CSS and Javascript, all while consistently testing my knowledge by creating 
        small projects. I can proudly say that programming has changed my life completely, as it has not only 
        taught me many invaluable lessons, but has also given me a great purpose in life. 
      </p>
      <a href="/download" class="anchor-btn mt-20">Resume</a>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="vp-100 projects" id="projects">    
    <div class="ml-50">
      <h3 class="secondary-header">Work I've Done</h3>
      <h3 class="header">&#8211; My Projects</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="projects-container">
      <div class="proj-hs full">
        <article class="project-item">
          <h3 class="project-title vm-10">Tower Defense 3D - Enemy Wave</h3>
          <img src="../imgs/tower-defense-3d-icon.png" height="223" width="350" alt="Tower Defence 3D - Enemy Wave">
          <section class="description-container">
            <figcaption class="vp-10">
              A tower defence game developed using Unity, and 
              playable on mobile, web and as standalone on PC/Laptop.<br><br>
              Features:
              <p>- Programmed clean, modularized and reusable scripts with scriptable objects and object-orientated programming</p>
              <p>- Utilized binary serialization to save and load user progress</p>
              <p>- Created complex stats for tower, enemy and special items</p>
            </figcaption>
            <figcaption class="project-label">
              <h3 class="mb-10">Languages / Libraries / Softwares</h3>
              <div class="project-skills">
                <h5>C#</h5>
                <h5>Unity</h5>
                <h5>Photoshop</h5>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </section>
          <div class="mt-auto">
            <a href="/tower-defence-3d-enemy-wave" class="anchor-btn vm-auto">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-item">
          <h3 class="project-title vm-10">Basketball Score App</h3>
          <img src="../imgs/basketball-score-app-icon.PNG" height="223" width="350" alt="Basketball Score App">
          <section class="description-container">
            <figcaption class="vp-10">
              A basketball score app where users can view and compare NBA player stats. Users may also search for scheduled NBA games and view match up.<br><br>
              Features:
              <p>- Integrated an open source API to fetch player, team and game data</p>
              <p>- Implemented useRef, useState and useEffect for getting and rendering data</p>
              <p>- Created functionality to sort, store and remove players from an array</p>
            </figcaption>
            <figcaption class="project-label">
              <h3 class="mb-10">Languages / Libraries / Softwares</h3>
              <div class="project-skills">
                <h5>HTML</h5>
                <h5>Sass</h5>
                <h5>JavaScript</h5>
                <h5>React</h5>
                <h5>Axios</h5>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </section>
          <div class="mt-auto">
            <a href="/basketballapp" class="anchor-btn vm-auto">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-item">
          <h3 class="project-title vm-10">bLogPoster</h3>
          <img src="../imgs/blogposter-icon.PNG" height="223" width="350" alt="blogPoster Website">
          <section class="description-container">
            <figcaption class="vp-10">
              A blog website where users can register and login to create blogs using HTML and CSS. Users may also view, comment and like other published blogs.
              <br><br>
              Features:
              <p>- Implemented nodemailer to send verification codes to user for account verification and for password reset</p>
              <p>- Implemented GET, POST, PUT and DELETE request for blogs and user routes</p>
              <p>- User, blog, comment and reply data is stored in MongoDB</p>
            </figcaption>
            <figcaption class="project-label">
              <h3 class="mb-10">Languages / Libraries / Softwares</h3>
              <div class="project-skills">
                <h5>JavaScript</h5>
                <h5>Node.js</h5>
                <h5>Bcrypt</h5>
                <h5>Express</h5>
                <h5>Mongoose</h5>
                <h5>Passport</h5>
                <h5>Nodemailer</h5>
                <h5>JSDOM</h5>
                <h5>Marked</h5>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </section>
          <div class="mt-auto">
            <a href="https://blogposter-website.herokuapp.com/bLogPoster"  target="_blank" class="anchor-btn vm-auto">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-item">
          <h3 class="project-title vm-10">Top Kicks Website</h3>
          <img src="../imgs/top-kicks-icon.png" height="223" width="350" alt="Top Kicks Website">
          <section class="description-container">
            <figcaption class="vp-10">
              A shoe company website where users can view the home page, as well as register or login to their accounts.
              <br><br>
              Features:
              <p>- Used @hapi/joi to create a template for registeration and login validation</p>
              <p>- Used bycrpt library to hash passwords for user security</p>
              <p>- Used flash library to display error/success messages to user</p>
              <p>- Used passport library for user authentication</p>
            </figcaption>
            <figcaption class="project-label">
              <h3 class="mb-10">Languages / Libraries / Softwares</h3>
              <div class="project-skills">
                <h5>HTML</h5>
                <h5>CSS</h5>
                <h5>JavaScript</h5>
                <h5>Node.js</h5>
                <h5>Bcrypt</h5>
                <h5>Express</h5>
                <h5>MongoDB</h5>
                <h5>Mongoose</h5>
                <h5>Passport</h5>
                <h5>@hapi/joi</h5>
                <h5></h5>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </section>
          <div class="mt-auto">
            <a href="https://top-kicks-website.herokuapp.com/home"  target="_blank" class="anchor-btn vm-auto">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-item">
          <h3 class="project-title vm-10">Weather App</h3>
          <img src="../imgs/weather-app-icon.png" height="223" width="350" alt="Weather App">
          <section class="description-container">
            <figcaption class="vp-10">
              A weather app created using REST API from openweathermap.org. You can search for a city 
              and the app will return the weather information of that city.<br><br>
              Features:
              <p>- Integrated Google maps API to fetch latitude and longitude coordinates</p>
              <p>- Fetched endpoint data from APIs with axios</p>
              <p>- Converted JSON data from the weather API into a readible format</p>
            </figcaption>
            <figcaption class="project-label">
              <h3 class="mb-10">Languages / Libraries / Softwares</h3>
              <div class="project-skills">
                <h5>HTML</h5>
                <h5>CSS</h5>
                <h5>JavaScript</h5>
                <h5>Node.js</h5>
                <h5>Express</h5>
                <h5>Dotenv</h5>
                <h5>Axios</h5>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </section>
          <div class="mt-auto">
            <a href="/weatherapp" class="anchor-btn vm-auto">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article class="project-item">
          <h3 class="project-title vm-10">Todo List App</h3>
          <img src="../imgs/todo-list-icon.PNG" height="223" width="350" alt="Todo List App">
          <section class="description-container">
            <figcaption class="vp-10">
              A todo list app where users can create several todo lists and add tasks to each of their todo lists.<br><br>
              Features:
              <p>- Implemented local storage to save and load data</p>
              <p>- Implemented create, delete and rename functionality with the use of map, find and filter functions</p>
              <p>- Created small single-purpose functions for easy code readability</p>
            </figcaption>
            <figcaption class="project-label">
              <h3 class="mb-10">Languages / Libraries / Softwares</h3>
              <div class="project-skills">
                <h5>HTML</h5>
                <h5>Sass</h5>
                <h5>JavaScript</h5>
                <h5>React</h5>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </section>
          <div class="mt-auto">
            <a href="/todolist" class="anchor-btn vm-auto">View Project</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

